prefix: Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in mathematics would.
problem_prompt:
Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in mathematics would. Below is a drawing of all $26$ letters in the English alphabet. As drawn below, some of these letters could be portions of the graph of a function, and some cannot. For example, the $\textsf{O}$ resembles an ellipse, which cannot be part of the graph of a function.

As drawn below, which of these letters could be portions of the graph of a function? (You may not rotate them.)

Give your answer as a list of letters with no spaces or other punctuation between them, in alphabetic order.

$$\begin{array}{c c c c c}
\textsf{A} & \textsf{B} & \textsf{C} & \textsf{D} & \textsf{E}\\\\
\textsf{F} & \textsf{G} & \textsf{H} & \textsf{I} & \textsf{J}\\\\
\textsf{K} & \textsf{L} & \textsf{M} & \textsf{N} & \textsf{O}\\\\
\textsf{P} & \textsf{Q} & \textsf{R} & \textsf{S} & \textsf{T}\\\\
\textsf{U} & \textsf{V} & \textsf{W} & \textsf{X} & \textsf{Y}\\\\
&& \textsf{Z} &&
\end{array}$$
gpt_response:
Let's consider the definition of a function. A function is a relation between a set of inputs and a set of possible outputs where each input is related to exactly one output. 

Looking at the letters provided, we can eliminate letters that cannot be portions of the graph of a function due to the fact that they fail the vertical line test. This means that for any vertical line drawn through the graph, it should intersect the graph at most once.

After examining the letters individually, we find that the following letters could be portions of the graph of a function: $\textsf{A, B, C, D, E, K, L, N, P, R, S, U, V, W, X, Y}$. 

Therefore, the list of letters that could be portions of the graph of a function, in alphabetical order, is: $\textsf{A B C D E K L N P R S U V W X Y}$.
